  "_notes": {
    "page_ids_source": "All 53 page_ids obtained via live sendme query on .40 (2026-04-13). No page 3 or 15 exists in the TFT.",
    "nav_bar": "Page 14 (tool) is the Tools/Settings page. Most nav button taps produce generic page report events — the TFT handles navigation internally.",
    "internal_navigations": "Many navigations are handled by TFT firmware internally without unique UART touch events. These pages are detected via 0x66 page reports.",
    "settings_vs_tools": "There is no separate 'settings' page in the TFT. The 'tool' page (14) contains both tools and settings buttons. Previously split across 'tools' and 'settings' in old screen_map — now unified under 'tool'.",
    "print_pages": "print=13 is the file browser, choose=10 is the source selector (local/usb/history), local=35 is local file list, usb=22 is USB file list, history=11 is print history.",
    "calibration_pages": "herdware=27 is the calibration menu. auto=37 is auto-level, c_cail=56 is manual calibration, cutt_arco=58 is cutter calibration, cutt_cail=57 is cutter sub-cal, check=8 is check page, cutt_checking=40 is cutting check.",
    "numpad": "Numpad on settem/extruder embeds ASCII digits before the 0x65 touch event. cid=170 is the numpad update, cid=18 is enter/confirm.",
    "release_only_buttons": "Some buttons only fire RELEASE events, not PRESS.",
    "missing_flow_page": "SetFlowPage uses PAGE_NAME='flow' but there is no 'flow' page in the TFT. Flow control may be part of setsp (page 33). Needs investigation.",
    "touch_page_ids_vs_report_ids": "Touch events (0x65) may carry the same page IDs as 0x66 page reports (confirmed for home=12, settem=32). Binary voronFDM used 0x99 frame type with DIFFERENT page numbering (1-15). The binary_touch_map in manager.py uses the binary's numbering scheme."
  }
